      "reviews": [
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDOI5fDsM5M3_SD",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "d997bb4"
          },
          "author": "chris-wood",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:18:03Z",
          "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 6,
              "body": "```suggestion\r\n  PROTOCOL: I-D.draft-ietf-privacypass-protocol\r\n```",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:18:03Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 7,
              "body": "```suggestion\r\n  BLINDRSA: I-D.draft-irtf-cfrg-rsa-blind-signatures\r\n```",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:18:10Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 24,
              "body": "```suggestion\r\n- Public Metadata: Arbitrary length metadata that can be viewed by the Client, Attester, Issuer, and Origin. Public metadata is bound Tokens issued by the issuer and therefore cannot be changed.\r\n```",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:20:09Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 34,
              "body": "```suggestion\r\n{{Section 6 of PROTOCOL}} in that the issuance and redemption protocols carry metadata provided by the Client and visible to the Attester, Issuer, and Origin. This means Clients can set arbitrary metadata when requesting a token, but specific values of metadata may be rejected by either Attester, Issuer, or Origin. Similar to a token nonce, metadata is cryptographically bound to a token and cannot be altered.\r\n```",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:22:45Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 40,
              "body": "I think we may want to include key generation details in this document, in particular because the PBRSA variant requires a very specific type of key.",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:23:22Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 57,
              "body": "```suggestion\r\n- Metadata value: `metadata`, an opaque byte string of length at most 2<sup>16-1</sup> bytes.\r\n```",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:35:03Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 60,
              "body": "```suggestion\r\nthis protocol are described below. The constant `Nk` is defined as 256 for token type 0x1234 in\r\n```",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:35:18Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 60,
              "body": "... assuming we go with 2048-bit keys",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:35:42Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 71,
              "body": "```suggestion\r\ntoken_input = concat(0x1234, // Token type field is 2 bytes long\r\n                     len_in_bytes(metadata), // 2-byte length of metadata\r\n                     metadata,\r\n```",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:37:31Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 71,
              "body": "This is so that the signature covers everything preceding the authenticator in Token. That said, it's redundant... since `Blind` will concatenate the input to the metadata, and could therefore be more expensive than desired.",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:40:30Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 79,
              "body": "The current draft requires PrepareRandomize, not PrepareIdentity, so this may need some work.",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:40:56Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 76,
              "body": "Blind also returns the randomized prefix that's appended to the message.",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:41:38Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 104,
              "body": "What does \"that all blinded_msg values are encoded for\" mean?",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:42:39Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 133,
              "body": "I would drop \"satisfies issuer requirements\" since it's not clear what that means. I would instead lean on text elsewhere that says something like \"metadata values are defined by the deployment and have privacy considerations; see <architecture doc> for more details.\"",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:45:13Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 110,
              "body": "Since this is a new TokenRequest structure, we need a new media type.",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:45:42Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 156,
              "body": "We'd also need a new media type for this, too.",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:45:52Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 177,
              "body": "This new Token type will need a new media type, too. I wonder if we should name these something else so there's no confusion between these types and the existing ones.",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:48:00Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 196,
              "body": "\ud83d\udc4d Yeah, this looks like it still needs to be updated.",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:48:17Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 218,
              "body": "I assume this key generation advice has to be updated still?",
              "createdAt": "2023-02-08T18:48:47Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-02-08T18:52:53Z"
            }
          ]
        },
